WEBVTT

00:02.611 --> 00:04.134
♪♪

00:04.178 --> 00:06.354
Look, I know you think
all us dumb Americans

00:06.397 --> 00:08.138
are gonna try and get
a reaction out of you, but --

00:08.182 --> 00:10.227
Oh, God, he's out of control!
Runaway wheelchair!

00:10.271 --> 00:11.228
Abandon your posts!

00:11.272 --> 00:12.882
[ Tires squeal ]

00:12.925 --> 00:14.188
Respect.

00:14.231 --> 00:16.538
I finally have the relationship
with my father

00:16.581 --> 00:18.105
I've always wanted,

00:18.148 --> 00:21.238
but if I ask him for the money,
I could lose him forever.

00:21.282 --> 00:22.761
Have you ever experienced
anything like that?

00:24.285 --> 00:25.590
Oh, you have a great
relationship with your father,

00:25.634 --> 00:26.983
Yeah.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.550
Oh, it's your mother
who's the problem? Hmm.

00:28.593 --> 00:30.813
Mom!
Why are we sightseeing?

00:30.856 --> 00:33.250
We need to be asking Grandpa
for the money for the house.

00:33.294 --> 00:34.295
I can't take this!

00:34.338 --> 00:36.384
Okay, can I
tell you a secret?

00:36.427 --> 00:39.256
I just got off the phone
with Grandfather,

00:39.300 --> 00:41.128
and he's going to
give us the money.

00:44.653 --> 00:47.351
But listen --
under no circumstances

00:47.395 --> 00:50.050
can you ever mention
the money to him.

00:50.093 --> 00:51.486
It's a British pride thing.

00:51.529 --> 00:54.315
Thank you, Mom.
I never should have doubted you.

00:55.272 --> 00:56.447
Don't judge me!

00:56.491 --> 00:58.275
I'm gonna get the money.

00:58.319 --> 01:02.062
I just, I hate the fact that I'm
gonna break my father's heart.

01:02.105 --> 01:03.280
Oh, good idea.

01:03.324 --> 01:06.109
Give myself this last day
to have fun with him

01:06.153 --> 01:09.330
and savor his love
before perhaps never see--

01:09.373 --> 01:10.287
Don't walk away!

01:11.288 --> 01:13.508
Oh. Oh. Shift change.

01:13.551 --> 01:14.900
So, what's yourdad like?

01:14.944 --> 01:17.120
Against all odds,
it's happening again!

01:17.164 --> 01:18.121
Take cover!

01:18.165 --> 01:19.122
[ Tires squeal ]

01:19.166 --> 01:20.341
We got a flinch.

01:20.384 --> 01:21.516
We got a flinch!

01:21.559 --> 01:24.910
Together:
U.S.A.! U.S.A.! U.S.A.!

01:24.954 --> 01:28.914
--Captions by VITAC--

01:28.958 --> 01:31.134
♪♪

01:31.178 --> 01:32.701
That was me
last time I was here.

01:32.744 --> 01:34.398
Touring with my band.

01:34.442 --> 01:35.269
Simpler times.

01:35.312 --> 01:36.313
Sound like greattimes.

01:36.357 --> 01:37.749
Oh, the best.

01:37.793 --> 01:39.925
This cool club we played is
actually right down the street.

01:39.969 --> 01:40.926
I could show you.

01:40.970 --> 01:42.711
No, man,
that sounds too boring.

01:42.754 --> 01:44.365
Plus, I gotta
get down to business.

01:44.408 --> 01:45.279
Trip's almost over.

01:45.322 --> 01:48.195
I gotta find myself
a whirlwind romance.

01:48.238 --> 01:49.413
Mind if I practice?

01:49.457 --> 01:50.762
"I didn't come to this pub

01:50.806 --> 01:53.548
expecting to meet
the girl of my dreams."

01:53.591 --> 01:56.986
"But you're only here
for a few days."

01:57.029 --> 01:58.988
"Then let's make
the most of it."

01:59.031 --> 02:02.383
Ah. To be single and however
young you try to be.

02:02.426 --> 02:03.427
Godspeed.

02:03.471 --> 02:05.908
[ Punk rock playing ]

02:05.951 --> 02:07.910
B-- Is this you?

02:07.953 --> 02:10.042
I was literally coming over
to put this song on.

02:10.086 --> 02:12.001
Brilliant song.
Best second album of all time.

02:12.044 --> 02:14.264
I dunno. I'd probably
go with "Metal Box" --

02:14.308 --> 02:16.179
by the band
on your shirt!

02:16.223 --> 02:18.834
Good taste in music.
Are you here on holiday?

02:18.877 --> 02:21.228
No, I'm here because
my wife has to ask her father

02:21.271 --> 02:22.533
for a loan
to save our house.

02:22.577 --> 02:23.882
Similar boat here.

02:23.926 --> 02:26.233
I got laid off recently.
Now I work for my father-in-law.

02:26.276 --> 02:27.712
I just feel like
such an...

02:27.756 --> 02:30.106
Ineffectual waste of space.Ineffectual waste of space.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.239
♪♪

02:32.282 --> 02:33.283
Jimmy.

02:33.327 --> 02:34.371
Rowan.

02:34.415 --> 02:37.244
I didn't come to the pub
expecting to make a new friend.

02:37.287 --> 02:39.811
But I'm only here
for a few days.

02:39.855 --> 02:41.248
Then let's make
the most of it.

02:42.510 --> 02:44.425
Embarrassing confession --

02:44.468 --> 02:47.819
I have never seen
a London sunrise.

02:47.863 --> 02:48.733
Huh.

02:48.777 --> 02:49.995
I should probably
head home.

02:50.039 --> 02:51.432
I've got work
in the morning.

02:51.475 --> 02:52.781
Oh.

02:52.824 --> 02:54.348
Oh. Excuse me, bud.

02:54.391 --> 02:56.001
I'm kind of in the middle
of something. [ Chuckles ]

02:58.221 --> 02:59.744
"I'm JJ.

02:59.788 --> 03:02.791
Kenneth is my --"
C-A-- "caregiver and...

03:02.834 --> 03:04.488
superhero."

03:04.532 --> 03:05.794
That's so sweet!

03:05.837 --> 03:07.752
I think I may have
underestimated you.

03:07.796 --> 03:09.319
Ahh.
I'd love to get
to know you better.

03:09.363 --> 03:13.236
Especially since I'm actually
moving to California next month.

03:13.280 --> 03:14.629
Oh. Well, it was nice
to meet you.

03:14.672 --> 03:17.022
I gotta get this scamp home
to bed. Bye. [ Chuckles ]

03:18.807 --> 03:19.808
Phew.

03:20.852 --> 03:23.812
"See what I did there,
superhero?"

03:23.855 --> 03:25.248
Uh, yeah,
that was good

03:25.292 --> 03:27.381
until she turned into
a stage-5 clinger.

03:28.947 --> 03:31.559
"I can be your wingman."

03:31.602 --> 03:33.169
I appreciate that,

03:33.213 --> 03:35.867
but I have a bad history when
it comes to adorable wingmen.

03:35.911 --> 03:39.001
One time, I was backstage
at a Spice Girls show,

03:39.044 --> 03:42.222
and Mel B. andMel C.
wanted me.

03:42.265 --> 03:44.572
But then I had to drive
my dumb nieces home.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.400
Why go to a concert
when you have a bedtime?

03:47.401 --> 03:50.491
Oh, I don't know.
We got this whole house thing.

03:50.534 --> 03:53.058
You did say
Maya'sout having fun.

03:53.102 --> 03:55.365
♪ But I don't care You're right.

03:55.409 --> 03:57.541
It's not like she's somewhere
crying right now.

03:57.585 --> 04:00.065
[ Sobbing ]

04:00.109 --> 04:01.850
Don't be sad
that you're leaving.

04:01.893 --> 04:03.634
Look, I'll be
coming regularly --

04:03.678 --> 04:05.114
Christmas, birthdays,

04:05.157 --> 04:07.116
that stupid American holiday

04:07.159 --> 04:08.683
when everyone eats
too much turkey

04:08.726 --> 04:11.163
and says how dreadful it was
at the airport.

04:11.207 --> 04:15.298
From now on, Maya,
I am gonna stay in your life.

04:15.342 --> 04:17.518
If there's anything at all
that you want --

04:17.561 --> 04:19.868
anything --
just say the word.

04:22.174 --> 04:23.219
Anything?

04:23.263 --> 04:24.307
Anything.

04:24.351 --> 04:28.268
So...
if I had a problem now,

04:28.311 --> 04:29.399
you'd fix it?

04:29.443 --> 04:30.661
Of course.

04:32.576 --> 04:34.665
[ Punk rock playing,
crowd cheering ]

04:37.407 --> 04:39.540
Look! That's me,
playing this club!

04:39.583 --> 04:40.889
Rowan:
You're a rock god!

04:41.977 --> 04:43.413
Do you want me
to take that?

04:43.457 --> 04:44.762
Yeah!

04:44.806 --> 04:46.329
Oh, friendship is awesome!

04:48.853 --> 04:51.595
I'm really glad
I met you, Rowan.

04:51.639 --> 04:54.337
Between work and family,
it's just -- I don't know.

04:54.381 --> 04:55.817
I don't have time
for friends anymore.

04:55.860 --> 04:58.385
Yeah.
I feel the same way.

04:58.428 --> 04:59.647
I wish you weren't
leaving so soon.

04:59.690 --> 05:02.911
Well, doesn't change
what we shared tonight.

05:02.954 --> 05:05.522
BFFs?
British friends forever?

05:09.004 --> 05:10.397
This is me.

05:10.440 --> 05:11.572
Oh.

05:13.008 --> 05:14.618
Do you...want to come up?

05:14.662 --> 05:17.839
♪♪

05:17.882 --> 05:20.494
[ Record crackling ]

05:20.537 --> 05:22.626
[ Both snoring ]

05:22.670 --> 05:26.674
♪♪

05:29.938 --> 05:33.245
♪♪

05:33.289 --> 05:34.899
I'm actually feeling
pretty good about this.

05:34.943 --> 05:36.553
As long as Father thinks
the house problem is new

05:36.597 --> 05:38.033
and not the reason
we came to London,

05:38.076 --> 05:39.339
then he's gonna
give us the loan

05:39.382 --> 05:41.297
and also get
to feel like a hero.

05:41.341 --> 05:43.517
Always good to make family feel
good about themselves

05:43.560 --> 05:44.866
beforeyou trick them
into giving you money.

05:46.694 --> 05:47.651
[ Knock on door ]

05:47.695 --> 05:48.870
Now, children, remember,

05:48.913 --> 05:53.527
one never speaks to one's
grandfather about money loaned.

05:53.570 --> 05:56.573
Ohh. The nuanced rules here --
they're fascinating!

05:56.617 --> 05:57.879
-Ah!
-Oh, hello, Father.

05:57.922 --> 05:59.359
Is there somewhere quiet
we could talk?

05:59.402 --> 06:00.621
No!

06:02.405 --> 06:05.495
Together: Surprise!

06:05.539 --> 06:07.976
Aunt Emma. Andrew.

06:08.019 --> 06:11.545
I thought our reunion
called for a celebration.

06:11.588 --> 06:14.243
I want them to see
how much I love my daughter.

06:14.286 --> 06:15.462
Do you hear that?

06:15.505 --> 06:18.160
I like my daughter!

06:18.203 --> 06:21.032
Out loud,
it seemed a bit vulgar.

06:21.076 --> 06:23.034
-Maya, nice to see you.
-This is our family.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.602
All our lives,
it's just been us.

06:25.646 --> 06:28.170
Let's go connect.
We're a part of something.

06:28.213 --> 06:29.606
Aren't you excited?

06:29.650 --> 06:31.608
Eh. I been
part of stuff before.

06:31.652 --> 06:33.393
So, your sister's
a track star

06:33.436 --> 06:34.698
and your brother's
a filmmaker.

06:34.742 --> 06:35.699
What are you?

06:35.743 --> 06:38.441
Um...
no one thing, really.

06:38.485 --> 06:39.486
I guess I'm multifaceted.

06:39.529 --> 06:42.445
Oh. And what are
some of these facets?

06:42.489 --> 06:44.708
Well, I love
connecting with family,

06:44.752 --> 06:46.493
so this is me
in my element.

06:46.536 --> 06:48.451
Well, I wouldn't exactly
say we're connecting.

06:48.495 --> 06:50.627
I have no idea
who you are.

06:50.671 --> 06:51.802
Who are you?!

06:53.848 --> 06:55.676
Hey, Dad,
can I borrow your phone?

06:55.719 --> 06:57.765
I do not have my phone.

06:57.808 --> 07:00.463
I forgot it
at a friend's place --

07:00.507 --> 07:02.552
like a guy with a friend
would say.

07:02.596 --> 07:04.902
My God.
Josephine.

07:04.946 --> 07:06.208
Yeah, how you doin'?

07:06.251 --> 07:07.339
You're Dylan.

07:07.383 --> 07:08.471
Just trying
to keep it quick, man.

07:08.515 --> 07:09.516
You don't understand.

07:09.559 --> 07:11.561
You're the spitting image
of my sister.

07:11.605 --> 07:12.606
Josephine?

07:12.649 --> 07:14.042
She passed away
last year.

07:14.085 --> 07:15.609
Tough stuff.
Better place.

07:15.652 --> 07:18.525
Uh [Chuckles] Dylan...
this is you.

07:19.526 --> 07:21.571
Is that a tiger?!

07:21.615 --> 07:23.443
Dead Me rocks!

07:23.486 --> 07:27.621
♪♪

07:27.664 --> 07:32.582
"So, which of these ladies
am I wingmanning you for?"

07:32.626 --> 07:33.888
You mean of these ladies

07:33.931 --> 07:36.020
who all resemble
and remind me of your mom

07:36.064 --> 07:37.848
at this 10:00 a.m. party?

07:37.892 --> 07:38.806
I'm good.

07:38.849 --> 07:43.680
♪♪

07:43.724 --> 07:45.595
Don't point
at anyof them.

07:45.639 --> 07:47.379
I don't want
any cousin butt!

07:49.643 --> 07:51.906
Right. I've said my hellos.
Let's talk to Father.

07:51.949 --> 07:53.821
We'll say the house has been
sold out from under us.

07:53.864 --> 07:55.344
Whoa!
I need more than that.

07:55.387 --> 07:56.650
What were we doing when
the phone call came through?

07:56.693 --> 07:57.651
Well, who cares?

07:57.694 --> 08:00.175
I need detail.
Bad improviser.

08:00.218 --> 08:02.046
I was talking to family.
You were on the terrace.

08:02.090 --> 08:03.395
Ah, I'm never gonna
remember all that.

08:03.439 --> 08:04.788
Should I find
someone else to help?

08:06.137 --> 08:08.618
No. I think I got a way
to make your terrace pitch work.

08:09.750 --> 08:12.056
The trick is to grab your wrist
with your other hand.

08:12.100 --> 08:12.970
Oh, come on, pal.

08:13.014 --> 08:14.842
At least tryand get out.

08:14.885 --> 08:16.234
I kid. I kid.

08:16.278 --> 08:17.366
He's a good sport.

08:17.409 --> 08:18.889
She has Josephine's
wit, too.

08:18.933 --> 08:20.761
Oh, you think she'sfunny?

08:20.804 --> 08:21.805
Please.
I'mthe funny one.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.285
Are you?
Say something funny.

08:23.328 --> 08:26.375
Oh. I mean, I can't just, like,
do it out of nowhere.

08:26.418 --> 08:28.246
Give me something to work with.
How was your day?

08:28.290 --> 08:30.292
Well, we drove up
from Sussex this morning...

08:30.335 --> 08:31.423
[ Scoffs ]
That's nothing.

08:31.467 --> 08:34.775
Uh, did you see a fat guy?
Did he fall down?

08:34.818 --> 08:36.733
Ray, check out
Dead Me's tiger.

08:36.777 --> 08:39.736
[ Gasps ] Oh, my!
That's very interesting.

08:39.780 --> 08:40.781
[ Scoffs ]

08:40.824 --> 08:43.958
♪♪

08:44.001 --> 08:45.612
What's wrong, son?

08:45.655 --> 08:47.527
Ha ha. "Ray matters."

08:47.570 --> 08:48.658
Really funny.

08:49.616 --> 08:51.356
Oh. Wait.
You're actually asking?

08:51.400 --> 08:53.271
I was,but to quote
your generation,

08:53.315 --> 08:55.883
you've gone
and made it weird.

08:55.926 --> 08:57.101
Oh, I'm so sorry.

08:57.145 --> 08:59.321
I've just been trying
to connect with family here,

08:59.364 --> 09:00.888
and I can't seem
to break through.

09:00.931 --> 09:03.107
Well, if you want to connect
with your English relatives,

09:03.151 --> 09:04.631
it's, uh,
perfectly simple.

09:04.674 --> 09:06.589
Good manners,
graciousness,

09:06.633 --> 09:09.374
and knowing when
to end a conversation.

09:09.418 --> 09:10.724
Graciousness, eh?

09:10.767 --> 09:13.335
Well, there is someone
I want to very much thank

09:13.378 --> 09:15.119
for their generosity
to my family,

09:15.163 --> 09:16.773
but I was forbidden.

09:16.817 --> 09:19.080
Are you telling me
they would want that?

09:19.123 --> 09:20.342
I think that would be
the quickest way

09:20.385 --> 09:21.561
of getting out of this.

09:21.604 --> 09:22.736
Hmm.

09:22.779 --> 09:24.433
Everyone!
[ Groans ]

09:24.476 --> 09:26.478
A toast
to my grandfather.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.307
It's just us, boy.

09:29.351 --> 09:32.876
And what is it you want
so badly to thank me for?

09:32.920 --> 09:34.704
♪♪

09:34.748 --> 09:35.966
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

09:36.010 --> 09:38.447
Well, don't mind if I do.

09:38.490 --> 09:40.492
[ Chuckles ]

09:40.536 --> 09:41.624
Oh!

09:41.668 --> 09:43.844
I, uh,
never turn down cheese.

09:43.887 --> 09:44.845
[ Chuckles ]

09:44.888 --> 09:45.802
Oh!

09:45.846 --> 09:48.239
Someone took that
as a challenge.

09:48.283 --> 09:49.632
Challenge accepted.

09:49.676 --> 09:50.720
[ Chuckles ]

09:50.764 --> 09:52.940
Okay.

09:52.983 --> 09:55.812
Starting to get
a little strange.

09:55.856 --> 09:57.640
[ Chuckles ]

10:00.469 --> 10:03.690
Hey! Are you herding
cheese women to me?

10:03.733 --> 10:05.996
"You said...no relatives."

10:06.040 --> 10:07.607
What is wrong with you?

10:07.650 --> 10:09.391
Just leave me alone, man.

10:09.434 --> 10:10.914
Oh, he's coming.

10:10.958 --> 10:12.394
And...anguish.

10:13.525 --> 10:14.962
What are we gonna do?!

10:15.005 --> 10:17.834
I don't know, Jimmy.
I mean, it only just happened.

10:17.878 --> 10:18.748
What just happened,
darling?

10:18.792 --> 10:20.315
Oh, Daddy, I don't
want to burden you,

10:20.358 --> 10:22.273
but Jimmy just got
a very disturbing phone call.

10:22.317 --> 10:23.318
On the terrace.

10:24.972 --> 10:27.714
Apparently, our landlord
has sold the house,

10:27.757 --> 10:29.933
and we can't match the offer,
so we're going to have to move,

10:29.977 --> 10:31.805
and -- and the kids are gonna
have to leave school.

10:31.848 --> 10:33.458
Ohh.
And this just happened.

10:33.502 --> 10:34.808
Right in the middle
of your trip to London

10:34.851 --> 10:36.592
to show your love for me.

10:36.636 --> 10:38.289
What a dreadful
coincidence.

10:38.333 --> 10:39.943
Uh, not a coincidence.

10:39.987 --> 10:41.292
They probably called

10:41.336 --> 10:43.730
because they knew
we'd be out of the house.

10:43.773 --> 10:47.821
And why would
your landlord call at, uh...

10:47.864 --> 10:50.301
4:00 a.m. California time?

10:52.434 --> 10:54.131
Well...because...

10:54.175 --> 10:56.307
it was the lawyer who called,
and they're London-based.

10:56.351 --> 10:57.526
Ah!

10:57.569 --> 10:58.875
So, what's
the lawyer's name?

10:59.833 --> 11:00.964
Ask me, Daddy!

11:01.008 --> 11:02.705
No, no. No.
He was on the phone to him.

11:02.749 --> 11:03.967
You told me. Remember?Yes.

11:04.011 --> 11:05.490
So, what's
the lawyer's name?

11:09.233 --> 11:12.759
It is...just the beginning
of the questions, Jimmy.

11:13.803 --> 11:16.240
Surely you can
tell him a name.

11:16.284 --> 11:17.241
Uh...

11:17.285 --> 11:18.982
No? Perhaps
we can guess it.

11:19.026 --> 11:20.767
Uh, Christopher?
Matthew?

11:20.810 --> 11:21.942
Sebastian?

11:21.985 --> 11:23.465
Maya: Andrew? Colin?

11:23.508 --> 11:24.422
Peter?Steven?

11:24.466 --> 11:25.249
Jeffrey?Michael?

11:25.293 --> 11:26.555
Norman?Marlon?

11:26.598 --> 11:28.035
Something? Anything.

11:28.078 --> 11:29.906
Samuel!You did it!

11:29.950 --> 11:30.820
L...
No.

11:30.864 --> 11:32.909
...Jackson. I'm so sorry.
It just was.

11:32.953 --> 11:34.737
Look, I'd love to provide
the funds for this house,

11:34.781 --> 11:35.999
so let's talk to, uh,

11:36.043 --> 11:40.221
Mr., uh, Samuel L. Jackson,
Esquire, huh?

11:40.264 --> 11:41.309
Call him back.

11:42.223 --> 11:44.791
I...do not have
my phone.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.270
Well, we'll have to find
some way to find him.

11:46.314 --> 11:48.446
Because I really do
want to save your house,

11:48.490 --> 11:51.275
because I am so happy
that you came here

11:51.319 --> 11:53.495
just to show your love.

11:53.538 --> 11:55.062
You've known all along.

11:55.105 --> 11:56.063
How?

11:56.106 --> 11:57.717
I'm sensing
a little tension here.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.196
Might I suggest
a thank-you?

12:00.937 --> 12:02.504
You don't know
everything,Mom.

12:02.547 --> 12:03.984
♪♪

12:06.943 --> 12:10.338
♪♪

12:10.381 --> 12:11.556
Oh, hell no!

12:11.600 --> 12:13.776
Whatever this is,
I am not interested.

12:15.082 --> 12:17.258
"I know I haven't helped,

12:17.301 --> 12:20.914
but trust me,
this will be worth it."

12:22.829 --> 12:23.917
I was told to say,

12:23.960 --> 12:27.572
"This van is only for cool dudes
who know how to party."

12:27.616 --> 12:29.792
Did he tell you to say it
half-assed like that?

12:29.836 --> 12:31.011
I know how to party.

12:31.054 --> 12:31.794
Let's go.

12:33.100 --> 12:34.449
Yes,
I came for the money,

12:34.492 --> 12:36.886
but then I got you,
which was worth so much more.

12:36.930 --> 12:39.019
And then I couldn't ask you,
for fear I'd hurt you.

12:39.062 --> 12:41.151
So you want the love
andthe money.

12:41.195 --> 12:42.892
So, let's just recap,
right?

12:42.936 --> 12:43.893
Both...

12:43.937 --> 12:44.894
love...

12:44.938 --> 12:46.113
money...

12:46.156 --> 12:47.375
neither.

12:47.418 --> 12:49.246
Oh, bloody hell,
I didn't think about neither.

12:49.290 --> 12:50.857
But the connection
was real.

12:50.900 --> 12:54.034
Well, I'll give you
a chance to prove it, okay?

12:54.077 --> 12:56.123
If you want my love,
it's yours.

12:56.166 --> 12:58.255
If you want the money,
take it.

12:59.213 --> 13:01.084
I cannot give you both.

13:01.128 --> 13:06.002
♪♪

13:06.046 --> 13:08.352
The memo is
"Goodbye forever"?

13:08.396 --> 13:11.747
I mean,
I hate the dilemma...

13:11.791 --> 13:13.401
but hats off
for the drama.

13:14.402 --> 13:16.883
If you'd told me three days ago
that we would get the money

13:16.926 --> 13:18.667
and I would never have to speak
to my father again,

13:18.710 --> 13:20.103
I would've said,
"Great! What's the catch?"

13:20.147 --> 13:21.452
I really thought
I'd connected with him

13:21.496 --> 13:23.280
off the strength
of my graciousness.

13:23.324 --> 13:26.457
Roger Whitney...Bill Hughes...
Takahara Yoshimoto...

13:26.501 --> 13:27.719
I can't cash this.

13:27.763 --> 13:28.851
[ Knock on door ]

13:28.895 --> 13:30.548
-Who's there?
-No clue.

13:30.592 --> 13:32.550
The day really
can't get any worse.

13:33.987 --> 13:36.250
Oh, good.
Have you come to gloat?

13:36.293 --> 13:37.294
No, I'm here to help.

13:37.338 --> 13:38.730
Now, I know
you've never cared for me --

13:38.774 --> 13:40.080
Ugh! Get on with it.

13:41.298 --> 13:42.647
Apologies.

13:42.691 --> 13:44.127
I am a lady.
I will behave as such.

13:44.171 --> 13:45.128
Do go on.

13:45.172 --> 13:45.955
Martin is broke.

13:47.130 --> 13:48.088
[Bleep] you say?

13:48.131 --> 13:49.480
That check is worthless.

13:49.524 --> 13:51.700
He was too proud
to let you know the truth.

13:51.743 --> 13:53.310
I do hope
you have a relationship,

13:53.354 --> 13:55.922
but if you do,
it can't be based on a lie.

13:55.965 --> 13:57.445
Oh, you're helping.

13:57.488 --> 13:58.794
How on Earth
did I ever think

13:58.838 --> 14:01.014
you were anything
other than absolutely lovely?

14:01.057 --> 14:04.582
Well, back then, you really were
a spoiled-rotten little cow.

14:04.626 --> 14:07.281
Yeah. Just when I thought you
were too nice to actually like.

14:07.324 --> 14:09.109
[ Chuckles ]

14:09.152 --> 14:12.199
Well, now that it's all
out on the table...

14:12.242 --> 14:13.853
you gonna go
put an end to this?

14:15.115 --> 14:16.507
I'm gonna screw him
to the wall.

14:19.075 --> 14:20.381
UH, are we there yet?

14:20.424 --> 14:21.948
Also,
where are we going?

14:21.991 --> 14:22.905
[ Beeping ]

14:24.907 --> 14:27.214
One of the two
that got away?!

14:27.257 --> 14:31.740
"Your wingman is here...
to help you soar."

14:31.783 --> 14:34.438
Kind of lame, but I can't argue
with your results.

14:34.482 --> 14:38.094
So, which one is it --
Mel B. or Mel C.?

14:41.141 --> 14:43.012
Mel D.?! What?!

14:43.056 --> 14:44.927
Jimmy: Kids,
meet Daddy's friend.

14:47.930 --> 14:48.975
-Jimmy.
-Hey, bud.

14:49.018 --> 14:50.890
Uh, in the whirlwind
of hanging out

14:50.933 --> 14:52.674
and connecting
'til the sun went down,

14:52.717 --> 14:55.459
I somehow forgot my phone.
[ Chuckles ]

14:55.503 --> 14:56.983
Classic
best-friend mistake.

14:57.026 --> 14:59.942
Jimmy, you really should have
called before coming over.

14:59.986 --> 15:01.204
Man:
Who's out there, Rowan?

15:02.466 --> 15:04.381
Y-You have company.

15:04.425 --> 15:06.166
Who's this, then?

15:06.209 --> 15:07.515
Who are you...
then?

15:07.558 --> 15:08.951
Nigel, meet Jimmy.

15:08.995 --> 15:10.474
Jimmy, meet Nigel...

15:10.518 --> 15:11.998
my best friend.

15:12.041 --> 15:13.216
Ahh.

15:13.260 --> 15:15.044
Jimmy, I didn't want you
to find out this way.

15:15.088 --> 15:16.916
The truth is,
I'm not friendless.

15:16.959 --> 15:18.221
I just really
connected with you,

15:18.265 --> 15:20.136
and I wanted you
to connect with me.

15:20.180 --> 15:23.139
But this doesn't take away
what we had.

15:23.183 --> 15:30.190
♪♪

15:30.233 --> 15:31.931
Hey, um...

15:31.974 --> 15:33.367
you enjoy this man.

15:33.410 --> 15:35.543
Oh, I do.

15:35.586 --> 15:37.023
Strange intonation there.

15:37.066 --> 15:38.067
Weird.

15:41.636 --> 15:43.029
Father, I've given this
a lot of thought.

15:43.072 --> 15:44.247
What we've found here

15:44.291 --> 15:47.076
is something I never
allowed myself to hope for.

15:47.120 --> 15:48.556
I love you.

15:48.599 --> 15:50.079
But I have chosen
the check.

15:51.994 --> 15:53.604
Really?

15:53.648 --> 15:55.171
W-W--
Instead of the love?

15:55.215 --> 15:56.825
I'm afraid so.

15:56.868 --> 16:00.916
Yes, I...think I s-see
what is happening here.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.788
You want the love,
but you like a good deal.

16:03.832 --> 16:07.183
So, what about my love...

16:07.227 --> 16:08.532
and this vase?

16:08.576 --> 16:09.794
No, thank you.

16:09.838 --> 16:12.058
The love is nice,
but you can't live in it.

16:12.101 --> 16:13.015
Metaphorically, you can.

16:13.059 --> 16:14.408
You're broke!No, I'm not!

16:14.451 --> 16:15.844
Yes, you are!
Frances told me!

16:15.887 --> 16:18.673
Stupid nice people!

16:18.716 --> 16:20.327
There's no talking to them,
is there?

16:23.025 --> 16:24.070
Buck up, Jimbo.

16:24.113 --> 16:25.158
It's better
to have liked and lost

16:25.201 --> 16:27.203
than to have never
liked at all.

16:27.247 --> 16:29.162
I just made that up.

16:29.205 --> 16:30.946
Why am I not
better at school?

16:30.990 --> 16:32.904
You think that's
what I'm thinking about?

16:32.948 --> 16:34.210
I'm on the house, man.

16:34.254 --> 16:36.473
It's okay to be upset
about your friend, too.

16:36.517 --> 16:39.955
Fine --
I suppose I do miss

16:39.999 --> 16:42.262
the kind of friends I had
before life got in the way.

16:42.305 --> 16:43.785
I-I did have them.

16:43.828 --> 16:45.308
See, that's -- that's real.

16:45.352 --> 16:47.136
I did not photoshop myself
into this.

16:47.180 --> 16:49.008
Might make you feel better
to get in touch.

16:49.051 --> 16:51.184
-Ugh.
-Text them.

16:51.227 --> 16:53.882
If it will take us off
the all-important topic

16:53.925 --> 16:55.666
of Daddy's friendships,
I will.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.407
Okay? You happy?

16:57.451 --> 16:59.366
You're way cooler
than that Nigel dork.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.020
He is a dork!
Thank you!

17:03.152 --> 17:04.458
Why are you forcing this?

17:04.501 --> 17:06.547
I don't need you
to be my wingman.

17:07.504 --> 17:10.464
"Then what am I
going to be?"

17:10.507 --> 17:12.814
What does that mean?

17:12.857 --> 17:16.078
"I saw something
at your place --

17:16.122 --> 17:17.688
job applications."

17:17.732 --> 17:18.863
Oh.

17:18.907 --> 17:21.301
JJ, I'm exploring
my options.

17:21.344 --> 17:23.564
I always figured
I'd work for you

17:23.607 --> 17:26.784
until you graduated high school,
and that's happening.

17:26.828 --> 17:29.048
I should have
said something.

17:29.091 --> 17:31.137
"I'm not mad.

17:31.180 --> 17:35.271
I don't expect you
to be my aide forever."

17:35.315 --> 17:38.144
So why did you need to show me
you could be a wingman?

17:40.102 --> 17:42.887
"If I had
something to offer,

17:42.931 --> 17:44.759
we could stay friends."

17:46.543 --> 17:48.067
"Stay friends"?

17:48.110 --> 17:49.894
Dude.

17:49.938 --> 17:52.245
I don't know what the next step
is for either of us,

17:52.288 --> 17:55.509
but this --
it's not going anywhere.

17:55.552 --> 17:56.727
You know that.

17:58.425 --> 17:59.730
You don't know that?

18:01.384 --> 18:03.212
JJ, know that.

18:03.256 --> 18:07.695
♪♪

18:07.738 --> 18:09.523
Have you been standing there
this whole time?

18:09.566 --> 18:12.221
I don't have
a lot of fans.

18:12.265 --> 18:13.266
We're not fans!

18:13.309 --> 18:14.310
Not yet.

18:16.138 --> 18:17.531
What kind of act is this?

18:18.793 --> 18:20.882
Ugh! I can't take
all the up-and-downs!

18:20.925 --> 18:21.970
You're not like a father!

18:22.013 --> 18:23.711
You're like
a crazy college boyfriend!

18:23.754 --> 18:27.280
And you're like the dancer that
I cheated on your mother with.

18:27.323 --> 18:28.411
You knew about that,
right?

18:28.455 --> 18:30.674
Everyoneknew about that!Oh, fine.

18:30.718 --> 18:32.328
Why can't we just
have a normal relationship

18:32.372 --> 18:36.071
without the lying
and the drama and scheming?

18:37.420 --> 18:39.379
[ Hoarsely ]
Because I'm dying of cancer.

18:39.422 --> 18:40.336
[ Normal voice ]
Worth a try.

18:40.380 --> 18:43.339
Can we just talk for once
like normal people?

18:43.383 --> 18:44.340
I suppose.

18:45.646 --> 18:48.562
Daddy, I need
to borrow some money.

18:48.605 --> 18:50.390
May I have some?

18:50.433 --> 18:53.132
I don't have any
to give you.

18:53.175 --> 18:55.438
I still love you.

18:55.482 --> 18:58.789
Well, that sounds like
the sort of back-and-forth

18:58.833 --> 19:01.792
that might not lead to
20 more years of estrangement.

19:01.836 --> 19:05.883
♪♪

19:05.927 --> 19:07.146
Less fun, though.

19:07.189 --> 19:08.843
♪♪

19:08.886 --> 19:10.801
[ Pigeons cooing ]Pigeons in England
are way slower.

19:10.845 --> 19:12.107
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]

19:12.151 --> 19:13.326
Are you gonna check that?

19:13.369 --> 19:14.936
Nobody ever texts me
but the Red Cross.

19:14.979 --> 19:16.242
Universal donor!

19:16.285 --> 19:17.721
Take that, Nigel.

19:17.765 --> 19:20.115
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]Who's "Phil Lead Guitar"?

19:20.159 --> 19:21.290
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]

19:21.334 --> 19:23.466
Oh. He, uh,
used to be in my band.

19:23.510 --> 19:25.381
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]There's Carl, too.

19:25.425 --> 19:27.209
Your phone's blowing up.

19:27.253 --> 19:28.602
[ Cellphone chiming, buzzing ]I have friends.

19:28.645 --> 19:30.386
I have not-Rowan friends!

19:30.430 --> 19:31.387
[ Cellphone bloops ]

19:31.431 --> 19:32.910
Mom's texting me.

19:32.954 --> 19:35.304
Hear that? All of Ray's friends
are texting him, too.

19:35.348 --> 19:36.610
[ Laughs ]

19:36.653 --> 19:38.481
Oh.
I'm killing you.

19:42.398 --> 19:45.401
Mom said to meet back at the
hotel to say goodbye to Grandpa.

19:45.445 --> 19:47.273
Uh, you guys go ahead.

19:47.316 --> 19:49.362
I will catch up.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.015
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]Friend text.

19:51.059 --> 19:53.061
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]Friend text.

19:53.104 --> 19:56.499
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]Ohh! Massive multi-car accident
in Anaheim. Donors needed.

19:56.543 --> 19:58.022
[ Cellphone chimes, buzzes ]Ah! Friend text!

19:59.372 --> 20:02.201
Goodbye, everyone.
Sorry I couldn't save the house.

20:02.244 --> 20:04.507
We got something
even better.

20:04.551 --> 20:06.205
I'm referring to you.

20:06.248 --> 20:07.989
He's not one
for subtlety, is he?

20:08.032 --> 20:10.383
I find the wrong ones
tend to be nonverbal.

20:10.426 --> 20:13.429
Aw, Daddy, we'll be fine,
house or no house.

20:13.473 --> 20:15.388
This trip has been
a bigger success

20:15.431 --> 20:17.390
than I could ever
have dreamed of.

20:17.433 --> 20:19.740
Jimmy: [ Through P.A. ]
I got the house!

20:19.783 --> 20:21.350
I got the house!

20:21.394 --> 20:22.612
What?!

20:22.656 --> 20:24.440
Maya, you're never
gonna believe this.

20:24.484 --> 20:26.442
I got back in touch
with the guys from my band.

20:26.486 --> 20:28.401
Carl is a loan officer.

20:28.444 --> 20:30.794
Weird Pete
is a mortgage broker

20:30.838 --> 20:32.448
Glen...sells weed.

20:32.492 --> 20:34.494
Not as useful,
but still good to know.

20:34.537 --> 20:36.191
They're gonna help us
get the house!

20:36.235 --> 20:38.019
Jimmy, that's amazing!

20:38.062 --> 20:39.499
We're not alone!

20:39.542 --> 20:41.283
When we open our hearts
and we're honest,

20:41.327 --> 20:42.632
we find we have family!

20:42.676 --> 20:44.504
In many forms.

20:44.547 --> 20:47.463
Good God, son,
let it be subtext.

20:47.507 --> 20:49.248
Come on.
We're gonna celebrate --

20:49.291 --> 20:51.424
by ruining the tour
for everybody else.

20:51.467 --> 20:53.339
You are not getting
the microphone back.

20:53.382 --> 20:56.255
[ Punk rock plays ]

20:56.298 --> 20:58.344
♪ On a tour
of one-night stands ♪

20:58.387 --> 21:01.303
♪ My suitcase and guitar
in hand ♪

21:01.347 --> 21:03.827
♪ And every stop
is neatly planned ♪

21:03.871 --> 21:08.267
♪ For a poet
and a one-man band ♪

21:08.310 --> 21:11.270
♪ Homeward bound

21:11.313 --> 21:13.359
♪ I wish I was

21:13.402 --> 21:17.406
♪ Homeward bound

21:17.450 --> 21:20.148
♪ Home,
where my thought's escaping ♪

21:20.191 --> 21:22.672
♪ Home,
where my music's playing ♪

21:22.716 --> 21:24.457
♪ Home,
where my love lies waiting ♪

21:24.500 --> 21:25.458
[ Electricity crackles ]Ow!

21:25.501 --> 21:26.937
-Uh-oh.
-Ohh.

21:26.981 --> 21:28.287
We gotta move.
